                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 21558/3.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Vice and Deputy Consul General <persName type="from"
                            >Cauldwell</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                        State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Alexandria</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-10-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 2, 1909</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Egyptian ministry for foreign affairs says it is unable to arrest Memar Rizk, as
                    he is a Syrian, but will arrest him on request of Turkish Government. Meantime
                    Rizk will be searched out and watched.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cauldwell.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
